Reasoning: The paper deals with the capacity of a quantum channel for transmitting classical and quantum information simultaneously, which falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also discusses the transmission of private classical information, which is related to classical cryptography (cs.CR). The use of position-based decoding and convex-split lemma suggests that the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and mathematical physics (cs.MM).
